news.title: Online application must for Kolkata civic body's nod to new building plans
news.para: Manual application will be allowed only to seek approval of plans for additions and alterations to existing structures and reconstruction of insecure buildings, mayor Firhad Hakim said on Saturday.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board gets Rs 48 crore under transfer of property tax
news.para: The CEO added that another 20 crore is even now pending with the state govt and urged the govt to release the remaining TPT charges.

news.title: Odisha RERA asks builders to submit bank account details of projects
news.para: As per the rules, the promoters need to maintain a separate bank account for each of the housing projects if they have taken booking amount from the homebuyers.

news.title: Panvel civic body serves prior-to-seizure notices to 300 property tax defaulters
news.para: They include 101 industrial units, 107 non-residential properties and 100 residential properties. The civic body area has 3.50lakh properties. The property tax matter has reached the Supreme Court.

news.title: HC directs ED to probe promoters of 3C, berates Noida authority for 'acting like private trader'
news.para: Calling it a "classing case of conning", the court ordered the developers to cooperate with the ED and said the central agency "would be free to take any appropriate action against them as available under the law".

news.title: Documents related to projects should be delivered at headquarter: UP-RERA
news.para: According to this office order, promoters have been directed to deliver the documents related to project registration, extension, editing, etc., either personally or post, at UP-RERA Head Office, Lucknow.

news.title: Naukri, 99acres, few apps back on Google Play Store
news.para: ​IT and Telecom Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw, in an interview with PTI, said removal of apps cannot be permitted and that "startups will get the protection they need".

news.title: ED conducts searches on premises of real estate firms in Chennai
news.para: Iyra Builders and Vishnu Granites were some of the targets by the ED to gather evidence of money laundering and financial misconduct, said sources.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust acquires 1.4 million sq ft IT SEZ project in Pune for Rs 7.73 billion
news.para: Approximately 60% of BlueRidge 3 Phase 1 has been leased to multinational companies. Leasing for the rest of Phase 1 is underway.

news.title: Maharashtra's property registration department achieves 83% of revised 2023-24 revenue target
news.para: Ahead of the end to the financial year on March 31 and announcement of the new Ready Reckoner (RR) rates, the department has been earning over Rs3,500 crore every month, a registration department said on Friday.

news.title: Hyderabad set to get bigger as government plans greater city corporation
news.para: While the GHMC urban agglomeration sprawls across 625 square kilometres, HMDA has an area of 7,300 sq km under its purview.

news.title: Pune civic body to start work today on three town planning schemes in Uruli & Phursungi
news.para: Chief minister Eknath Shinde and deputy chief ministers Devendra Fadnavis and Ajit Pawar will be present at the programme.

news.title: Greater Noida authority allots Rs 500 crore for airport, Rs 1,200 crore for land acquisition
news.para: ​Overall, a budget of Rs 4,859 crore was approved for 2024-25 for GNIDA during its 134th Board Meeting held in Greater Noida.

news.title: Info Edge's 99 acres disappear from Google Play Store
news.para: ​This comes a day after Google began removing some apps, including popular matrimony apps, from its Play Store in India over a dispute on service fee payments.

news.title: NGT asks Ghaziabad DM to ascertain correct position of residential construction on land that's part of lake
news.para: The NGT was hearing a plea claiming that a project of Mahalaxmi Land and Finance Company was being built on a lake area in violation of environmental norms.

news.title: Telangana PCB slaps notice on Ananda Homes & Pooja Homes for encroaching Neknampur lake
news.para: The firms were found to have unlawfully encroached upon the lake and disposed of debris into it without authorisation, officials stated.

news.title: Over 1,700 defaulters owe Pune civic body Rs 5,000 crore in property tax
news.para: According to the data revealed under RTI, almost 94 property owners went to court against the dues, which amount to Rs 988 crore, of which Rs 565 crore is from two owners. In addition, tax from mobile towers amounts to Rs2,427 crore.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Environmentalists concerned as draft DP opens 'flamingo lake' area for development
news.para: While NMMC has clarified that it is a draft DP and not the final report, and that they have only included the updated Cidco nodal plan, greens opine that the ‘flamingo lake’ area should have been reserved as a no-development zone.

news.title: Nisus BCD Fund invests over Rs 105 crore in Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate subsidiary
news.para: The investment has been made towards a land parcel of 12.16 acres in Manjari-Budruk locality of Pune. This funding is aimed at helping the Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate Group in accelerating its assets in Pune within the mid-income affordable housing space.

news.title: Mumbai: Beauvue Stiledivita directors booked for cutting corners on interiors of Worli flat
news.para: EOW files FIR, directors deny allegations. Rs 80 crore apartment on Dr Annie Besant Road. Complainant alleges breach of contract, advance payment, and inspection issues. Selection of marble, granite, and furniture involved.
